Motivating example: eDNA Shiny app

Shiny is an R package and framework for building interactive applications. It provides a set of functions for building a front end web interface (into a file ui.R) that gets updated based on a back end set of R custom rendering functions (server.R). We’ll be diving into this more later. You can also get quick gander at the geyser eruption example on the homepage shiny.rstudio.com.

Shiny represents the end point, or motivating use case, for today to interactively visualize your data, after cleaning it up using data wrangling techniques. Here’s an example of a Shiny app for environmental DNA (eDNA) data:

ecoquants.shinyapps.io/edna-vis
